{# Description: Raw copy/paste Jinja template for deterministic scheduler-apply validation (decision + guarded apply + handoff inventory) with explicit MA boot-wait guidance, component-shadow entity preference hardening, contract-invalid/no-candidate operator guidance, live decision-source fallback when last scheduler decision is never_attempted, control-capable helper-fallback eligibility alignment, runtime control-expected reason visibility, stable-helper/no-candidate action clarification, hotspot-triage diagnostics surfaces, core-health weighted verdict scoring, and additive MA-players refresh/capability-feed checks. #}
{# Version: 2026.04.27.43 #}
{# Last updated: 2026-04-27 #}

{# =========================
  Scheduler Apply Deterministic Validation (Component)
  Purpose:
    - Validate scheduler readiness + decision/apply audit payloads.
    - Confirm helper membership/authority/debounce guard posture.
    - Surface legacy-only handoff dependency scaffold status.
  Usage:
    1) Optional prep actions in this order:
       - spectra_ls.validate_scheduler
       - spectra_ls.run_scheduler_choice
       - spectra_ls.apply_scheduler_choice (dry_run true first)
       - spectra_ls.run_metadata_trial_bridge_scaffold (for resolver/trial alignment)
    2) Paste in Developer Tools -> Template.
    3) Use PASS/WARN/FAIL output to classify readiness and blockers.
  ========================= #}

