### Deterministic next action
{% if not shadow_exists %}
- Shadow sensor missing. Ensure `custom_components/spectra_ls` is loaded and entity registry has either `sensor.shadow_active_target` (current) or `sensor.spectra_ls_shadow_active_target` (compatibility).
{% elif scheduler_waiting_for_ma_boot or bridge_waiting_for_ma_boot %}
- Waiting for Music Assistant startup signals. Re-run this template after MA player list/control targets are available; avoid forcing apply/recovery during this boot window.
{% elif no_control_capable_reason == 'target_not_control_expected' %}
- Active runtime target is currently not expected to expose a direct control host. Treat as non-actionable host warning suppression state unless your target contract should be control-capable.
{% elif esp_handoff_status in ['pending_refresh', 'no_host'] and selected_target not in invalid %}
- Scheduler selection is present but ESP handoff is not ready (`{{ esp_handoff_status }}`). Refresh/check `sensor.ma_control_hosts` and `sensor.ma_control_host`, then re-run this template after host surfaces settle.
{% elif 'no_scheduler_candidate' in scheduler_blocking_reasons and helper_state not in invalid and auto_select_status == 'noop_already_selected' and (auto_select_selected_target in invalid or auto_select_selected_target == helper_state) %}
- Active target is stable in helper state but currently has no resolved control-capable scheduler route (typical for non-TCP playback targets like AppleTV wrappers). Select a control-capable target (or restore host contract for this target) before expecting scheduler candidate output.
{% elif 'contract_invalid' in scheduler_blocking_reasons and 'no_scheduler_candidate' in scheduler_blocking_reasons %}
- Scheduler has no valid control-capable candidate because required control contracts are unresolved (commonly control-host feed fail-closed). Verify `sensor.ma_control_hosts`/`sensor.ma_control_host` are resolved before apply attempts.
{% elif validation_verdict == 'FAIL' %}
- Scheduler validation failed. Run `spectra_ls.validate_scheduler` and resolve contract/registry blockers before apply attempts.
{% elif hotspot_level == 'high' and metadata_prep_blocking_reasons | length > 0 %}
- Hotspot level is high with metadata-prep blockers. Resolve metadata prep blockers first, then rerun bridge scaffold and this template.
{% elif authority_mode == 'component' and not players_change_refresh_sequence_seen and auto_select_status in ['write_applied','noop_already_selected','dry_run_ok'] and auto_select_corr is string and ('state-change:sensor.ma_players-auto-select' in auto_select_corr) %}
- MA-player-change auto-select is visible but options-refresh sequencing was not observed in attempt telemetry. Re-run `spectra_ls.build_target_options_scaffold` then trigger MA-player-change path and re-check this template.
{% elif contract_soft_surface_warnings | length > 0 and selected_target not in invalid and selected_in_options %}
- Target selection is stable, but host contract soft warnings are present. Monitor `sensor.ma_control_hosts` / `sensor.ma_control_host` quality before non-dry-run actions.
{% elif selected_target in invalid %}
- No selected scheduler candidate in current snapshot. Check decision reason for helper-fallback rejection or host/control-capability gaps, then rerun `spectra_ls.run_scheduler_choice` after contract/profile recovery.
{% elif validation_verdict == 'PASS' and scheduler_ready and bridge_verdict == 'PASS' and bridge_ready and candidate_count | int(0) > 0 and selected_in_options %}
- All green in this snapshot: scheduler + bridge are PASS and target/options are aligned. No action required.
{% elif validation_verdict == 'PASS' and scheduler_ready and selected_target not in invalid and selected_in_options %}
- Scheduler readiness is healthy and selected target/options are aligned. No scheduler-choice action required in this snapshot.
{% elif authority_mode != 'component' %}
- Apply is guard-blocked by authority. Run `spectra_ls.run_metadata_trial_bridge_scaffold` (it now performs automatic component-authority target recovery before trial checks).
{% elif not selected_in_options %}
- Selected target is not in helper options. Run `spectra_ls.run_metadata_trial_bridge_scaffold` to auto-sync options and recover a control-capable target.
{% elif apply_status in ['blocked_authority','blocked_debounce','blocked_reentrancy','blocked_option_mismatch','blocked_no_candidate'] %}
- Last apply was guard-blocked. Run `spectra_ls.run_metadata_trial_bridge_scaffold` to auto-recover target/options, then re-run this template.
{% elif metadata_bridge_validation.verdict is defined and metadata_bridge_validation.verdict != 'PASS' %}
- Run `spectra_ls.run_metadata_trial_bridge_scaffold` with dry-run defaults; it auto-recovers target/options first, then reports remaining bridge blockers.
{% elif apply_status in ['dry_run_ok','noop_already_selected','write_applied'] %}
- Scheduler apply path is healthy in this snapshot.
{% else %}
- Run one-shot deterministic sequence: run_metadata_trial_bridge_scaffold (automatic target recovery -> resolver -> trial), then re-run this template.
{% endif %}

